lead_paragraph: THE British writer Simon Gray died in 2008 after a long life of writing and smoking, smoking and writing. His prolific output included more than 30 plays as well as novels, screenplays and a series of memoirs collectively entitled “The Smoking Diaries.” But Gray never really made much of a mark in the United States. Only three of his plays made it to Broadway, the most celebrated being “Butley,” revived in 2006 with Nathan Lane in the lead.
